website_summaries.verdict: The luxurious Master & Dynamic MW65 headphones deliver wonderful Bluetooth audio and good noise cancellation for a high price.
pros: Ideal bass depth and crisp clarity throughout the frequency range
cons: ANC is very good, but not the best for the price

customer_reviews.title: I've been waiting for this...
customer_reviews.text: I've always been a big, big fan of Master and Dynamic. The MH40 has been my favourite headphone for the past 2-3 years, even though its wired; it's just beautiful and the detail in the music just cannot be found elsewhere. In my option the MW65 combines beauty, material, performance and technology just perfectly. Still retaining the same acoustic detail which is hard to do with ANC; normally this becomes very muffled and watered down, not with the MW65 though. I can't put these things down. I cannot recommend the MW65 enough.
customer_reviews.author: Rainman

customer_reviews.title: Sennhsier Momentum 3 & B&W PX are superior
customer_reviews.text: I've got all 3, the MW65 have a low volume, weak soundstage and just overall aren't strong performers. At this price point they're robbery, go and try for yourself! I guarantee if you pit these against the Momentums you'll not buy them, the Sennheisers are far better than the PX or MW65. It's night and day. Sennheiser Momentum 3 >> B&PX > MW65
customer_reviews.author: Zeb Mattey

customer_reviews.title: Fabulous combination of style and substance.
customer_reviews.text: So far the headphones have lived up to the hype I've read about them. Beautifully crafted from high quality leather and aluminium, making them aesthetically desirable and great to the feel. Light and extremely comfortable to wear, with simple buttons for easy moving between the functions. And last but not least, fabulous, balanced sound, not overly weighted towards bass but punchy and crisp. Fantastic value for money.
customer_reviews.author: sunil angris

customer_reviews.title: Impressive
customer_reviews.text: If you aim to have one, do not hesitate to get it.
customer_reviews.author: Ayut

customer_reviews.title: Uncomfortable not over ear.
customer_reviews.text: A great pair of headphones ruined by too small of ear cups so they aren’t over ear but they’re not on ear so they pinch my ears. I feel like I have small ears. I wish high end companies would learn from Bose on ear cup comfort. Also they only used Bluetooth 4.2 on a 500$ headphone that’s unacceptable. I really wanted to keep them but the comfort was a huge FAIL. If they changed that and the Bluetooth I’d be back in a heart beat.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: You're better off buying Sony WH-1000XM3
customer_reviews.text: Master n Dynamic MW65 Pros: Premium quality material - wearing one feels like a status symbol. You're the man! Sound quality - good quality, I say good because it does produce good sound quality. Cons: ANC - what ANC? I had to return my original order because I thought my product was defective and ANC was not working, tried ANC on. High, Low n Off...NO difference. Got my replacement n lo and behold, it is what it is. ANC feature suck! Bass - bass is ok, could be better for a $500 headphones Overall verdict: I returned it and bought myself another Sony WH-1000XM3. Cheaper but man oh man way better than these $500 M&D MW65.
customer_reviews.author: Henry J.

customer_reviews.title: These are good headphones but the volume just doesn't go high enough.
customer_reviews.text: These are very well designed and built but honestly, I was expecting a lot more power. Even with the volume at its highest it's not what you would want when a good song comes, it's very mediocre for a set of headphones this expensive. I had the Fill headphones before these and I think I'm returning these and getting the Fill again. Those HAVE POWER and crisp quality. These are just too weak. The sound quality is good but very weak. If you like to listen to some songs and pump up the volume, these are NOT the right choice.
customer_reviews.author: Raul Henderson

customer_reviews.title: Need to remake them made to cheap Bluetooth would not connect Way overpriced
customer_reviews.text: I have to return them because they would not sync with my phone the Bluetooth wasn't working and I found them too difficult to work with for the $499 price tag. So I ordered the Sony HW1000 M X3 so far I love days very happy and priced much better.
customer_reviews.author: Robert B.Hughes

customer_reviews.title: Buy it for the clarity and the looks
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality is great. They're super clear and detailed with a little bit of color/warmth. They sit nicely in-between super bright "audiophile" headphones and bass-boosted consumer brands. Great build quality and looks. Lighter than they look. Noise cancelling is useful, but not the best. Won't remove the world like XM3s. But does a good enough job on low-frequency background din. Comfort for me is decent. I have a big head and big ears. I had to stretch out the headband to reduce clamp. I appreciate the physical controls. There is no app, which I sort of consider a plus. Charges with other USB-C cables and chargers. No audio output via USB-C. Supports aptX HD.
customer_reviews.author: LT

customer_reviews.title: Beautiful Design and Sound ...
customer_reviews.text: I've got several pairs of Maser and Dynamic Headphones, and these don't disappointment. I spend a ton of time in planes (about 70 flights a year), and have been waiting for M&D to come out with Noise Canceling at the high end. The beauty of these headphones is that you can wear them for hours and hours at a time without worrying about chafing. The leather is incredibly smooth, the buttons are of a high quality, and the sound is amazing. The orange inner ear design is a notable as well. Never disappointed by any of the headphones (including the earbuds), and these are no exception.
customer_reviews.author: Scott Harrison

customer_reviews.title: My new favorite headphones! I love them!
customer_reviews.text: I'm so impressed by the clean sound. I have several generations of Bose, and I use Beyerdynamic DT770s for audio mastering work, but I wanted a wireless set, and earbuds weren't cutting it. These have such clear sound with a beautiful warm sound that's perfect for listening pleasure. Mostly rock, jazz, classical. Bose can sound great, but not this great. The construction is solid. The leather is so supple that the ear pads flex around my ears, and they have nice thickness so my ears don't touch. And the headset is very light and comfy.
customer_reviews.author: SL Smith

customer_reviews.title: Superb Headhpones
customer_reviews.text: These are great headphones. The material and tactile feel of all the buttons are very nice. The sound quality is excellent. Some other reviews say they are not loud, but they are plenty loud for me. The padding around the ears is maybe a smidge too small, but they are pretty comfortable despite that. The battery life is amazing. Keep watching that price because SOMETIMES they are less than $500 😉
customer_reviews.author: Ben Morgan

customer_reviews.title: Expensive but totally worth every penny
customer_reviews.text: It’s a but nice or buy twice.. spend the money you won’t be disappointed.. made extremely well no plastic at all.. just leather and aluminum the way things are supposed to be built.. they pair easy, sound quality is bar none the best I have heard. I’m an audiophile and I don’t mind spending the coin if the product is worth it.. so stop reading all the reviews and buy then already..
customer_reviews.author: eric m.

customer_reviews.title: Very good could be a lot better
customer_reviews.text: Comfortable the sound is amazingly crisp and clear for music. Not so much for calls (I can hear fine. people complain they cant hear me) my biggest gripe would be that these aren't nearly as loud as some of the other premium headphones. An app and an eq would be a huge plus. Overall I dont think they're worth the price because they fall short in the one area where I thought they should shine. I'm not a bass head but loudness while still having the overall decent sound would've made these the best out there
customer_reviews.author: nathaniel dickerson

customer_reviews.title: Smooooooth 😍
customer_reviews.text: Smooth!!!!!Feels like I'm floating in the air.. Amazing volume, just nice for the bass as I do not prefer too much of it, treble are amazing. The ANC are not dat bad as well, its on the safe level I must say coz U can still notice a lil sound while walking on the road(wev 70%-80% volume).
customer_reviews.author: Fatin Fasihah

customer_reviews.title: Amazing Headphones!
customer_reviews.text: The MW65 was my first Master & Dynamic purchase, and I can confidently say I will be a customer of Master & Dynamic's for a long time. The noise cancelling technology exceeded my expectations and is great for traveling. The sound quality is also a highlight of these headphones, crisp when it needs to be but also enough bass to give you the full sound of whatever you're listening to. These will comfortably sit on your head, and unlike some of the over-ear headphones I've had in the past, these won't start to feel heavy or cumbersome after a few hours. Great purchase, I highly recommend to anyone interested in noise cancelling Bluetooth headphones.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: BUY THE V MODA CROSSFADE 2 CODEC EDITION AND YOU'LL BE HAPPY!
customer_reviews.text: BUY THE V MODA CROSSFADE 2 CODEC EDITION AND YOU'LL BE HAPPY!
customer_reviews.author: MARK P.

customer_reviews.title: Enjoy for wired music and medium noise cancellation.  Fails for calls.
customer_reviews.text: Noise cancelling was fine and audio was expected for the price. Couldn’t be used for calls or as a headset. Either microphone issues (they couldn’t hear me) or volume so loud or in variant volume that I’d regularly have my eardrums abused. 3 iOS devices, 2 PCs and a Mac. Never “just worked” Returned to amazon because M&D has no adequate documentation other than “call us”: that’s not a solution. Put your help online guys. Hiding it behind closed doors makes it look like you don’t want some things known about your product. (Also- no usb-c charging and listening? Can’t use usb-c port for audio without an adapter? Unacceptable for $500)
customer_reviews.author: Aero

customer_reviews.title: ANC NOT ADEQUATE
customer_reviews.text: If you want sound quality - very balanced If you want ANC- don’t bother less than adequate. Very low volume- need phone and headphones at max most times. Style - great Construction- great
customer_reviews.author: Greg R.

customer_reviews.title: Come for the stunning audio, stay for the design integrity.
customer_reviews.text: Stunning audio. Really. My first purchase from Master & Dynamic and am beyond happy with this product. Luxury. Incredible quality and design features. Considered and so chic. Even the detail of the seemingly hydraulic adjustable strap is gorgeous. Absolutely nothing clunky about this set. Love the multi-mode options for active noise cancellation. Easy to shift mode based on environment and great “feedback” signaling which mode you’re in. Mic works great for calls/etc. Haven’t experimented with Google assistant yet but it already feels like a level up.
customer_reviews.author: Aine Kennedy

customer_reviews.title: Worth it if you prefer the design.
customer_reviews.text: If you really like sound quality and design above all else than this the pair for you. The active noise cancelling is good but not the best. Bose has a better noise cancelling ability and so does Sony, however the sound is incredible. They are also very premium feeling In the hands.
customer_reviews.author: danny g 424

customer_reviews.title: Worth the Money Hands Down
customer_reviews.text: Honestly, was a bit hesitant to change brands after being a loyal buyer of Bose for the past decade plus. I have a pair of Q35 comforts that have served me well on transatlantic flights. But I’m always open to trying something new, and these M&D headphones did not disappoint. It’s a bit more but you absolutely get what you pay for—honestly there’s not really anything to criticize if you are willing to spend the money. I also wanted a more fashion forward version, and the brown style was exactly what I was hoping for. Five stars all around.
customer_reviews.author: Michael BS

customer_reviews.title: Th
customer_reviews.text: The Master & Dynamic MW65 Active Noise Canceling (ANC) Wireless Headphones was a present for my husband the previous Christmas (it was purchased on Dec 19, 2019), and the year is not over yet, but the headphones already died. I believe that for the cost of $500, it has to live and serve a little longer. Do not you think?
customer_reviews.author: vera kareva

customer_reviews.title: Buy now!
customer_reviews.text: Overall, these headphones have more than met my expectations. I have had a relationship with Bose products for about a decade and I was looking for new noise cancelling headphones. I was looking for headphones that were comfortable, reproduced a good range of audio and had good noise cancelling features. These headphones meet all of those criteria and then some! Don’t flinch at the price tag, the purchase is well worth it.
customer_reviews.author: Taylor

customer_reviews.title: Unbeatable sounds quality however microphone sucks
customer_reviews.text: Phenomenal design and sounds quality, my Bose headphone is 5 level down in sounds clarity. Mediocre noise canceling. Although i liked this headphone alot, it's microphone was a deal breaker for me. nobody could hear me in conference calls or even regular phone calls. Tried join calls via mac and Samsung GS20, same problem on both.
customer_reviews.author: matt

customer_reviews.title: Bad item
customer_reviews.text: Don’t ever think about this item, small cup for ear, bad leather, hard to operate
customer_reviews.author: S.....M

customer_reviews.title: So Comfortable! The Noise Cancellation is Unbelievable!
customer_reviews.text: I will never fly without these ever again!!!! They gave me the same comfort a weighted blanket does. The made my flight so much more enjoyable and me so much more relaxed!! I also love listening to my podcasts around the house in them! I love my Airpods but they can definitely get uncomfortable at times, not these! LOVE THEM!!!!!! Would definitely recommend!!!
customer_reviews.author: Tammy R

customer_reviews.title: Incredible sound quality
customer_reviews.text: I fly often for work and recently decided I needed a pair of noise canceling headphones. I have had other pairs in the past but wasn’t satisfied with the noise canceling feature. A friend had recently purchased a pair and I was immediately sold. They look stylish yet professional, sound fantastic, and are surprisingly compact and easy to pack. Give them a shot and you won’t be disappointed.
customer_reviews.author: Christian

customer_reviews.title: Great Headphone with Minor issue
customer_reviews.text: Overall, this is a great headphone and can be a good candidate for almost all situation. However, there is a minor issue, I am not sure whether this only happens to me. Sometimes, microphone may be blocked by something (I still have no answer what blocks microphone, probably the foam) when I have online meeting, and I have to adjust the angle of how I wear it.
customer_reviews.author: nchen26

customer_reviews.title: More on-ear than over ear
customer_reviews.text: Too small than what it appears to be. Doesn’t really cover the whole ear. And my ears are not that big. These were just sitting on my ears and pressing. They look aesthetically appealing.
customer_reviews.author: Shopper

customer_reviews.title: Impressive
customer_reviews.text: They are very comfortable. The range on the Bluetooth is excellent. Battery life is excellent. The construction is solid. Well worth the cost.
customer_reviews.author: S. Devine

customer_reviews.title: Great headset but expensive
customer_reviews.text: Like the fact I can use it in passive mode if battery dies. Great sound in noise canceling mode.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: LOVE my new headphones!!
customer_reviews.text: I had the originals and was addicted to the great style and the luxe ear pads, but these are even better. The sound quality is sharper and I am shocked by how light they are. Couldn't hear the horns honking outside thanks to the excellent noise canceling- which I had on medium. And the look is, as with all of their products, elegant and cool.
customer_reviews.author: Kammireiss

customer_reviews.title: Bluetooth solid on light not on
customer_reviews.text: Anyone know why i do not have a solid white led on while connected to BT? Supposed to be on.
customer_reviews.author: Thomas N. Tallerico

customer_reviews.title: Amazing Pair of Headphones
customer_reviews.text: These are my second pair of M&D headphones, I first purchased my MH40's back in 2013 and while those are excellent headphones, I was looking for a wireless option. The MW65 are fantastic and a noticeable upgrade from the MH40's not just in audio quality but also in weight, I can wear these all day with little discomfort!
customer_reviews.author: Andrew S.

customer_reviews.title: Amazing!
customer_reviews.text: The sound quality and comfort on these headphones is unreal! After borrowing my boyfriend’s, I had to get a pair for myself. I love the brown color, really nice and unique. I’ve had Bose and beats in the past, and these completely surpass in quality, comfort and sound. Way better in my opinion! 100% worth it.
customer_reviews.author: Gerry Calabrese

customer_reviews.title: Deficient sound quality
customer_reviews.text: Sound quality significantly decrease when noise cancelling is turned off
customer_reviews.author: Armando

customer_reviews.title: These headphones are amazing!
customer_reviews.text: I’m a DJ and music producer in my 40s and this is the first time in my life I’ve been able to find an all around high quality headphone for DJ-ing and studio monitoring. So light weight and durable and the sound quality EQ is amazing! I wore them on the plane and the noise cancelling is out of this world. Ten out of ten!
customer_reviews.author: Zen. Freeman

customer_reviews.title: everything it's cracked up to be
customer_reviews.text: exactly as advertised. lightweight but sturdy. comfortable. great sound for music. great for conference calls.
customer_reviews.author: Bert and Tina

customer_reviews.title: Best headphones
customer_reviews.text: Very happy with this purchase. Super stylish design and I love the brown leather-it just feels classier than other headphones I see. Very comfortable to wear with great sound quality. Getting a lot of positive comments from ppl at work who ask where I got them from. Would definitely recommend
customer_reviews.author: ben

customer_reviews.title: Not the best sounding headphones
customer_reviews.text: Not sure how these got 5 stars on most of the reviews. Lamb skin and design ? Sound is good but not much bass. No app either. Sounding Did not justify the price tag.
customer_reviews.author: nitesh

customer_reviews.title: Terrific headset great sound, and great materials and design
customer_reviews.text: I really enjoy the look and style. The sound quality is one of the best I have heard. Great highs and lows.
customer_reviews.author: Brad

customer_reviews.title: Its good to use a device that supports aptxHD
customer_reviews.text: Even without the noise cancelling. Put the headphones on and you wont hear anything but your music. Base and acoustic on point . Your getting your moneys worth this headphones
customer_reviews.author: Jordan Stampley

customer_reviews.title: Not as good as I expected
customer_reviews.text: Sounds good but not very loud at all. Noise cancellation is average not top notch. Physical quality is the best I’ve ever owned. Not worth 500 dollars. Maybe should be 350
customer_reviews.author: Shane DiLorenzo

customer_reviews.title: Amazing
customer_reviews.text: Sound and quality is the best I’ve ever had. $500 is a lot of money but if you can afford it, it is well worth it. Noise canceling works perfectly too!
customer_reviews.author: jacqueline

customer_reviews.title: Excellent headphones
customer_reviews.text: These are extremely comfortable headphones, with great sound. I really like the 2 settings of noise reduction. They're very well made, sturdy, with a very nice balanced sound. These will be my new go to headphones.
customer_reviews.author: Joe

customer_reviews.title: For the Audio-file out there these are amazing!
customer_reviews.text: M&D have managed to really go that extra mile from their M60's with weight reduction with no drop in sound quality. The price is a little high but I loved the look and feel of them, so you have to sometimes pay for that right(?). I have done a quick video of them for anyone interested to see them out of the box in real life.
customer_reviews.author: Beardy_Man

customer_reviews.title: Exceptional design and sound quality
customer_reviews.text: Beautifully designed and engineered headphones. They feel well built and are super comfy and that’s before the sound quality. Having experienced a number of audio brands over the years (B&O, Beats, Bose) the sound experience is exceptional. Also like the different levels of noise cancellation, can’t wait to use them on a flight!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer
